I personally swear by <a href="http://unusedino.de/ec64/technical/aay/c64" class="postlink">All About Your C64</a> by Ninja/The Dreams as <em>the</em> 6502 reference. It includes an opcode chart like the above (often quite handy when blurring the line between code and data) and covers virtually ever other software detail in a concise form.<br /><br />You'll still be forced to test on hardware to check some particularly obscure details, say whether RRA carry out reflects the shift or add, but that's rare and frankly unavoidable.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=56">doynax</a> — Fri Aug 08, 2014 4:50 am</p><hr />
